OL,6,F"We can't place a vote for local
OL,7,Fcouncillors or the mayor. We're not
OL,8,Fentitled to do that because we pay
OL,9,Fcouncil tax and our vote is at our
OL,10,Fpermanent residence so for us that's
OL,11,Fin Wakefield.
OL,13,F"What are we paying for?"
OL,15,FThe row erupted after the council told
OL,16,Fowners of the site's 272 plots in
OL,17,FFebruary that their bills would double
OL,18,Fto #3,000 a year because of the
OL,19,Fgovernment's second home premium.
