OL,6,FThe council said HMRC's Valuation
OL,7,FOffice Agency (VOA) decided whether
OL,8,Fproperties were classed as domestic
OL,9,Fand therefore chargeable for council
OL,10,Ftax.
OL,12,FA spokesperson for the council said:
OL,13,F"The council tax team has been in
OL,14,Fdiscussions with some site residents,
OL,15,Fwho understand that they need to
OL,16,Fappeal to the Valuation Office Agency
OL,17,Fregarding the classification of their
OL,18,Fproperties, as the council does not
OL,19,Fhave any power to change this
OL,20,Fclassification and is legally required
OL,21,Fto comply with it."
